Body elongate. Preanal length greater than the caudal region (from the vent level to the end of the caudal peduncle), 53.1% of SL (50.8% in the 
paratype
). Head depressed, rounded in dorsal view. Snout blunt (
Fig. 3
). Eyes rounded, more than twice snout length and placed in a dorso-lateral position. Nasal barbels longer than eye diameter. Chin barbel of 
paratype
more than twice the eye diameter (deformed in 
holotype
). Mouth rictus reaching the level of the anterior margin of the eye. Tongue free, lanceolate.

Gill rakers (
Fig. 4
). Gill rakers sparse, tuberculate and flattened, with many prickles.
